Mr Usman Gomna, the newly appointed Commissioner of Police in Jigawa has assumed duty in Dutse.SP Abdu Jinjiri, the Police Public Relations’ Officer, made this known in a statement in Dutse on Monday. Jinjiri said Gomna took over from Mr Bala Senchi who has been elevated to the rank of Assistant Inspector-General of Police and redeployed to Force Headquartres, Abuja. ALSO READ Jonathan hails Ugwuanyi’s multi-partisan approach to governance ”He assumed duty as substantive Commissioner of Police, Jigawa Police Command, on Nov. 22, 2019. “The new commissioner solicited for the cooperation of the people of the state for a better service delivery.“He also called on all residents to be law abiding, and could be reached at anytime on his mobile phone -07038468846,” Jinjiri said. (NAN)